# =============================================================================
# npm configuration for TallyJ 4
# =============================================================================

# esbuild lifecycle script approval
#
# esbuild (used by Vite for fast bundling) runs a postinstall script to download
# the correct platform binary. This is safe and expected.
#
# npm does not currently support a stable project-level .npmrc key for approving
# individual packages (both "allow-scripts.*" and "approve-scripts.*" trigger
# "Unknown project config" warnings in recent npm versions).
#
# The supported way to approve it is to run this command once after a fresh clone:
#
#     cd frontend
#     npm approve-scripts esbuild
#
# We keep this comment here as documentation for the team and for CI setups.
